An '''ujigami''' is a guardian [[god]] or spirit of a particular place in the [[Shinto]] [[religion]] of [[Japan]].

[[category:Shinto]]

{{Reli-stub}}

{{expand}}

An '''ujigami''' is a guardian [[god]] or [[spirit]] of a particular place in the [[Shinto]] [[religion]] of [[Japan]]. Most '''ujigami''' live in natural places such as a forest or a lake. When people take the notice of Ujigami they build [[shrines]]  in their honor.

[[category:Shinto]]

{{Shinto-stub}}

